content.description:
Really fun route. The start is pretty much 5.8 until you hit the fun crimps when you start working up from the completion of the traverse.

 Beta for the crux: Â 

 Right hand to either sloper or 2 finger pocket, left hand far left to crimp, right hand to crimp sidepull above left hand, stand up to high left jug. More or less. Some of my friends do it slightly differently. It's all in the feet.
content.protection: 6 bolts with sport clip anchors. Also has two bolts behind the belay station to protect the belayer because the station is on a cliff and a climber fall might pull the belayer off.
content.location: Shares a start with Gypsy Wall's first route, Living on The Edge.

content.description: Quite secluded area just to the left of Gypsy Wall. It's the overhanging area and the routes (at the moment) are on the face of the overhang. You'll belay from Gypsy Wall area.
